{"title_page": "Kintetsu Nagoya Station", "text_new": "{{short description|Railway station in Nagoya, Japan}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{More citations needed|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Kintetsu Nagoya Station\n| native_name = \u8fd1\u9244\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = Kintetsu Corporation - Kintetsu Nagoya Station - 01.JPG\n| alt         = \n| caption     = Kintetsu Nagoya Station in May 2009\n| other_name  = \n| address     = [[Nakamura-ku, Nagoya|Nakamura]], [[Nagoya]], [[Aichi]]\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{Coord|35|10|8.9|N|136|53|3.5|E|type:railwaystation_region:JP-23|display=title;inline}}\n| operator    = [[Kintetsu Railway]]\n| line        = [[Nagoya Line (Kintetsu)|Nagoya Line]]\n| platforms   = 4 [[bay platform]]s, 5 tracks\n| connections = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Meitetsu Nagoya Station|Meitetsu Nagoya]] ([[Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line|Nagoya Main Line]])\n* [[File:Shinkansen jrc.svg|20px]] [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Shinkansen]]\n* [[File:JR Central Tokaido Line.svg|18px]] [[T\u014dkaid\u014d Main Line]]\n* [[File:JR Central Chuo Line.svg|18px]] [[Ch\u016b\u014d Main Line]]\n* [[File:JR Central Kansai Line.svg|18px]] [[Kansai Main Line]]\n* [[File:Nagoya Subway Logo V2 (Higashiyama Line).svg|18px]] [[Higashiyama Line]]\n* [[File:Nagoya Subway Logo V2 (Sakura-dori Line).svg|18px]] [[Sakurad\u014dri Line]]\n* {{Colorbull|#334fa0}} [[Aonami Line]]}} \nBus stop\n| structure   = Underground Train Station\n| code        = E01\n| opened      = 26 June 1938\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = 63,171 daily\n| pass_year   = FY2018\n| services    = \n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Kintetsu Nagoya Station'''|\u8fd1\u9244\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u99c5|Kintetsu Nagoya eki}} is a [[terminal station]] on the [[Kintetsu Nagoya Line]]. It is connected to [[Nagoya Station]] ([[JR Central]], [[Aonami Line]], and [[Nagoya City Subway]]) and [[Meitetsu Nagoya Station]] ([[Nagoya Railroad]]).\n\n[[File:\u8fd1\u9244\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u99c5\u306e\u99c5\u540d\u6a19.jpg|thumb|Kintetsu Nagoya Station Sign]]\n[[File:Kintetsu Corporation - Kintetsu Nagoya Station - Ticket Gate - 01.JPG|thumb|Kintetsu Nagoya Station - Ticket Gate - 01]]\n[[File:Kintetsu Corporation - Kintetsu Nagoya Station - Ticket Gate - 02.JPG|thumb|Kintetsu Nagoya Station - Ticket Gate - 02]]\n[[File:MT-Meitetsu Nagoya Station-ConnectingTicketGate.jpg|thumb|Connecting Ticket Gate to [[Meitetsu Nagoya Station]] platforms]]\n\n==Layout==\nThe station has four [[bay platform]]s serving five tracks on the first basement.\n;Nagoya Line (for {{STN|Kuwana}}, {{STN|Kintetsu Yokkaichi||Yokkaichi}}, {{STN|Tsu}}, {{STN|Ise-Nakagawa}}, {{STN|Osaka Namba}}, {{STN|Ujiyamada}}, {{STN|Toba}} and {{STN|Kashikojima}})\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=1|first=2|nidx=Nagoya Line|dir=served by local trains<br />4-car length|col=#0000CD}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=2|nidx=Nagoya Line|dir=served by semi-express trains<br />partly by express trains<br />5-car length|col=#0000CD}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=3|nidx=Nagoya Line|dir=served by express trains<br />partly by semi-express trains<br />6-car length|col=#0000CD}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=4|nidx=Nagoya Line|dir=served by limited express trains<br />8-car length<br />also for semi-express trains and express trains disembarking passengers in the rush hours|col=#0000CD}}\n{{Ja-rail-line|pfn=5|first=3|nidx=Nagoya Line|dir=served by limited express trains<br />8-car length|col=#0000CD}}\n\n{| style=\"border:1px solid black;\"\n|+Track layout of Kintetsu Nagoya Station and Komeno Station<ref>{{cite book|last=Kawashima|first=Ry\u014dz\u014d|title=Zenkoku Tetsud\u014d Jij\u014d Dai-Kenky\u016b: Nagoya Toshin-bu, Mie Hen|year=1996|publisher=S\u014dshisha|language=Japanese|isbn=978-4-7942-0700-5|page=168}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Kawashima|first=Ry\u014dz\u014d|title=T\u014dkaid\u014d Line: Zen-eki, Zen-sen, Zen-haisen No.4, Toyohashi Station - Nagoya Area|year=2009|publisher=K\u014ddansha